      <title>The Ultimate Sign of Customer Loyalty: Their Identity</title>
      <description>When customers willingly hand over their data to you, it&amp;rsquo;s the ultimate sign of trust in your company and your intentions&amp;mdash;a true reflection of the belief that you have their best interests at heart. No pressure, but that gives your business a lot to live up to. If customer data is important to your growing business&amp;rsquo; success, it&amp;rsquo;s vital that you let customers know at every turn, in every way you can, that you fully understand that handing over their data is an act of trust, that you appreciate their faith in you, and that you will return their loyalty by being loyal in return. You&amp;rsquo;ve got to get the word out that you&amp;rsquo;ll treat their data like the valuable asset that it is: You won&amp;rsquo;t abuse it, and you&amp;rsquo;ll use it to deliver the best experience possible to them and to make that experience better all the time. And then keep that promise.</description>
