      <title>Play With Fire(walls) And Get Burned: A Future Without Firewalls</title>
      <description>Plato tells of the ancient city of Atlantis, full of advanced technology and feats of engineering such as the world will never see again. The Atlanteans built great walls of exotic metals, striving to conquer the very ocean itself. But they were unable to stem the tide and the angry gods sank Atlantis and all its wonders to the bottom of the ocean.</description>
